# MedVirtual Meta Creative Handoff

Default priority: **graphics-handoff clarity** for the Filipino VA/graphics team — not strategy essays or Meta Ads Manager ops.

## Goal
Keep 15–30 ads in the hopper. Make “do this next” obvious.

## Brand
- Ad-facing: **MedVirtual** only (never MedVirtual.ai)
- Tagline: Staffing Solutions for Every Practice
- Font: Be Vietnam
- Colors: `#077999`, `#00B2E2`, `#0D546B`
- Official SVG logos; MedVirtual-only for Meta ads

## Service model
Hire dedicated full-time virtual staff who join the practice team.
Not a call center / managed front desk / software / “we run your front desk.”

## Files
- Public: web-safe handoff assets
- `.local-masters/`: huge video / .ai
- `_private/`: internal docs, spreadsheets, exports — never expose to graphics

## Real People
Active: **Treatment E — Studio Profile**
Full-bleed natural portrait · light white/cyan plate · Meet {Name} · exact public role · Available to interview · colored logo.
Pain + CTA in Meta copy only.

Never reintroduce Treatment C, checklist layouts, CTA strips, or dark muddy teal overlays **onto named Talent Pool people**.

## Role-Offer (separate — team favorites)
Checklist + role-pill + price/CTA layouts on **stock/AI** people live under Templates → Role-Offer.
See `.cursor/rules/medvirtual-role-offer-loved.mdc` and `public/role-offer-templates.html`.
Do not mix those comps onto Real People Studio Profile cards.

Launch 1: Jessica, Chelsea, Angelica, Mark.
Next: Carmen, Jennifer, Stories resizes.

## Site order
1. Brief  2. Templates (layout refs + Role-Offer)  3. Launch 1 / Launch 2  4. Real People (one page)
Reference far right: Brand Guide · Assets · Images

## Workflow
Real People: copy form → attach refs → design Studio Profile  
Role-Offer: edit data / in-page fields → design from loved layouts

No UTM / form QA / campaign shell / audience clutter on graphics pages.

## Claims
Do not invent HIPAA, new rates, savings %, performance, credentials, or availability.
Role-Offer price fields may keep the approved default from those comps until ops changes them.
